looming over
every encounter?

18:22.125 --> 18:24.958
Look, lots of people
he's crossed swords with

18:24.958 --> 18:27.125
have gone away
stuck and steaming.

18:27.125 --> 18:28.625
Most can't even get a lawyer

18:28.625 --> 18:30.875
to take on an individual case
of this nature.

18:30.875 --> 18:32.166
You know why?

18:32.166 --> 18:33.666
The downside's too steep

18:33.666 --> 18:35.875
and the upside's
too hard to see.

18:35.875 --> 18:38.083
And if you still hope
to get Wendy back somehow,

18:38.083 --> 18:39.708
I don't see how this can help.

18:39.708 --> 18:42.166
You said you had some
information on that front.

18:42.166 --> 18:44.125
Wendy and Rhoades
remain separated.

18:44.125 --> 18:45.375
Where is he living?

18:45.375 --> 18:46.791
The house.

18:46.791 --> 18:49.125
Part of the time.

18:49.125 --> 18:50.666
She is, too,
part of the time.

18:50.666 --> 18:52.916
-How?
-They call it nesting.

18:52.916 --> 18:54.541
It's bullshit.

18:54.541 --> 18:57.250
I tried it for a few weeks
between wives two and three.

18:57.250 --> 18:59.166
Yes,
the parents trade nights.

18:59.166 --> 19:01.250
The children stay
in the familial home.

19:01.250 --> 19:03.916
A utopian idea
that's supposed to

19:03.916 --> 19:06.500
impart a feeling of well-being
in the young ones

19:06.500 --> 19:10.083
during a turbulent time.
-Like I said, bullshit.

19:10.083 --> 19:12.833
And Wendy was at Krakow Capital
earlier today.

19:12.833 --> 19:15.041
-What? That fucker's hired her?
-Unclear.

19:15.041 --> 19:16.416
If we're not getting her back,

19:16.416 --> 19:18.916
I've heard about this guy,
Lenny Gustaferson --

19:18.916 --> 19:21.000
Dr. Gus.
He is supposed to be badass.

19:21.000 --> 19:24.000
I can't believe
she's considering Krakow.

19:24.000 --> 19:26.791
That's a bucket shop.

19:26.791 --> 19:29.041
I want to know where
she's working,

19:29.041 --> 19:30.666
the hours.

19:30.666 --> 19:33.708
Hold off on that Gus guy
until I say.

19:33.708 --> 19:36.041
Good.

19:37.291 --> 19:39.666
I know Katie.
I know that she has the allergy.

19:39.666 --> 19:42.125
How does a mother passing by
know more than her?

19:42.125 --> 19:44.166
I can't administer
serious medication

19:44.166 --> 19:45.291
just because
some rich lady

19:45.291 --> 19:47.166
-stopped --
-Stop talking.

19:47.166 --> 19:50.166
Topher, I am not leaving my kids
in the care of this idiot.

19:50.166 --> 19:51.416
Are you gonna do it now,

19:51.416 --> 19:53.625
or do I have to call
the rest of the board?

19:53.625 --> 19:56.166
I get it, Lara, but we can't
do this thing bang-bang.

19:56.166 --> 19:59.000
I need a licensed nurse
on premises at all times.

20:01.125 --> 20:03.083
Hey, Mo. It's Lara.

20:03.083 --> 20:05.291
Look, I know
you're working nights,

20:05.291 --> 20:06.875
but I need your help.

20:06.875 --> 20:10.041
Can you come do a shift here
at the Horace School right now?

20:10.041 --> 20:12.041
Oh, you're the best.

20:12.041 --> 20:14.625
My cousin will be here
in 45 minutes.

20:14.625 --> 20:15.958
I'll cover until then.

20:15.958 --> 20:18.416
Fully licensed.

20:20.041 --> 20:21.500
Bye.

20:28.125 --> 20:31.250
It'll take a long time
to fill Bart Schooner's seat

20:31.250 --> 20:33.333
as head of criminal prosecution.

20:33.333 --> 20:37.250
- Oh, at least 15 minutes...

20:37.250 --> 20:39.083
...until someone with
a law degree

20:39.083 --> 20:42.625
and a controlled drinking habit
stumbles in.

20:42.625 --> 20:44.041
Let me -- Let me get serious.

20:44.041 --> 20:48.291
I just want to talk
about Bart's...

20:48.291 --> 20:50.083
Head of Crim. Man.

20:50.083 --> 20:51.666
Plum perch.

20:51.666 --> 20:53.750
Freaking launch pad
to the private sector.

20:53.750 --> 20:55.833
I mean, you land it,
you're minted.

20:55.833 --> 20:58.000
Seven figures
the day you leave.

20:58.000 --> 20:59.333
How the hell
do you get it?

20:59.333 --> 21:01.833
There's 75 AUSAs in here
all going after it.

21:01.833 --> 21:04.083
You got to pay your dues.

21:04.083 --> 21:07.958
Yeah.
Big cases, ingeniously won.

21:07.958 --> 21:11.750
After years
of dutiful service.

21:11.750 --> 21:13.375
- Years and years.

21:13.375 --> 21:15.333
So I'm too young?

21:15.333 --> 21:17.083
You're getting that?

21:17.083 --> 21:18.958
Too green.

21:18.958 --> 21:21.416
It'll go to an old hand
like one of you two, then?

21:21.416 --> 21:23.291
"Experienced", not "old".

21:23.291 --> 21:25.958
- Seasoned.

21:25.958 --> 21:28.000
I'm out of scotch.

21:28.000 --> 21:31.166
See, I order two at a time
at these things

21:31.166 --> 21:34.166
because the waiters disappear
like Houdini after the entrées.

21:34.166 --> 21:35.958
You got to know that.
Plan ahead.

21:35.958 --> 21:37.666
Smart. Seasoned.

21:37.666 --> 21:39.041
Souses.

21:39.041 --> 21:40.375
What I'd like to know is,

21:40.375 --> 21:42.875
will Chuck still be the one
handing out the job?

21:44.333 --> 21:46.500
-The investigation.
-Hell yeah.

21:46.500 --> 21:48.791
They say Dake rides in
on a pale horse.

21:48.791 --> 21:51.125
What do you think
he's got on Chuck?

21:51.125 --> 21:53.333
Well, well, well.
Three young apprentices

21:53.333 --> 21:55.666
celebrating the departure
of a colleague.

21:57.083 --> 21:59.625
Sure.
But don't they also want to

21:59.625 --> 22:01.625
put a foot in his ass
and take his spot?

22:01.625 --> 22:03.458
Hmm?

22:03.458 --> 22:05.208
Oh, come on.

22:06.500 --> 22:09.291
You know Head of Crim
is the hyperloop

22:09.291 --> 22:12.833
that propels you into
whatever job you want next.

22:12.833 --> 22:14.791
How to get it --

22:14.791 --> 22:16.791
Let me tell you.

22:16.791 --> 22:21.083
Our practices
leave grooves over time.

22:21.083 --> 22:24.125
And eventually,
those grooves become walls

22:24.125 --> 22:26.791
that box us in.

22:26.791 --> 22:30.916
So what I figured out
recently is,

22:30.916 --> 22:32.125
find another way.

22:32.125 --> 22:35.541
♪ tense music  ♪

22:35.541 --> 22:39.083
I found myself in a chess match
in Washington Square Park

22:39.083 --> 22:41.083
with one of those hustlers

22:41.083 --> 22:44.166
who's been taking
tourists' money for years.

22:44.166 --> 22:45.958
A bit of a crowd
had formed.

22:45.958 --> 22:48.791
This was a hard-fought match.

22:50.416 --> 22:52.916
I had just gained an edge.

22:52.916 --> 22:57.625
I had an unstoppable waiting
attack when I saw it happen.

22:57.625 --> 23:01.000
He swiped both my knights
with one capture.

23:01.000 --> 23:04.166
Oh, the cheat was
very well executed.

23:04.166 --> 23:07.666
I was about to go across
the table at him.

23:07.666 --> 23:10.541
To make sure he was banned
from the park,

23:10.541 --> 23:12.875
to exact retribution.

23:12.875 --> 23:17.125
But then in an instant,
I saw...

23:17.125 --> 23:18.916
this was the chance

23:18.916 --> 23:23.083
to re-frame
my entire approach.

23:23.083 --> 23:25.541
So instead...

23:25.541 --> 23:28.541
♪ dramatic music playing  ♪

23:38.041 --> 23:40.250
I caught what you did.

23:40.250 --> 23:42.666
Takes practice to master
something like that.

23:42.666 --> 23:44.375
It's to be admired in a sense,

23:44.375 --> 23:47.208
but that is the last time
you use it today.

23:49.166 --> 23:52.416
I'm a man who could
make things difficult for you,

23:52.416 --> 23:54.833
but I won't.

23:54.833 --> 23:57.041
As long as
you'll understand this.

23:57.041 --> 24:00.625
Your next opponent
is that boy.

24:04.166 --> 24:07.833
And I want him to have a very
good time playing against you.

24:10.291 --> 24:11.708
Thank you.

24:11.708 --> 24:13.625
The man thanked me.

24:13.625 --> 24:16.916
Imagine that.

24:16.916 --> 24:20.166
And I knew he wasn't gonna
cheat anyone else that day

24:20.166 --> 24:23.166
and would look over his shoulder
thereafter.

24:23.166 --> 24:28.000
I had managed something
better than payback.

24:28.000 --> 24:30.458
By acting with purpose
and understatement,

24:30.458 --> 24:33.250
I had created
a more just environment,

24:33.250 --> 24:36.833
which is what I am asking
of all of you.

24:39.291 --> 24:41.000
This is the new way.

24:44.041 --> 24:47.125
Well, how do you know
if he did the right thing

24:47.125 --> 24:48.416
after you left?

24:48.416 --> 24:52.208
Uh, I sat on a nearby bench
and watched awhile.

25:10.916 --> 25:12.250
Thanks for coming.

25:12.250 --> 25:14.416
I know you'll think
it's worth the effort.

25:14.416 --> 25:16.875
-Quickly, Spyros.
-Okay.

25:16.875 --> 25:18.833
I always listen
to the ground.

25:18.833 --> 25:21.791
-It's how I got where I am.
-Mm-hmm. And?

25:21.791 --> 25:23.083
An investigation has begun

25:23.083 --> 25:26.000
into your office's
methods and conduct,

25:26.000 --> 25:29.458
focusing on an aborted
bribery case against Axelrod.

25:29.458 --> 25:31.583
And the man leading
the investigation

25:31.583 --> 25:35.125
is dangerous and capable.

25:35.125 --> 25:39.416
A younger, even smarter
version of me,

25:39.416 --> 25:42.125
if you can conjure that
for yourself.

25:42.125 --> 25:43.750
I scarcely can.

25:43.750 --> 25:46.000
Who is he?

25:46.000 --> 25:48.208
Oliver Dake.

25:53.958 --> 25:55.416
Are we square now?

25:57.125 --> 25:59.041
Don't serve rabbit food
to an elephant

25:59.041 --> 26:02.000
and ask if he's full.

26:02.000 --> 26:05.666
♪ dramatic music plays  ♪

26:14.666 --> 26:16.708
Sir.

26:16.708 --> 26:19.625
Would you get these fine young
barristers another round?

26:19.625 --> 26:21.458
-Of course.
-Thank you.

26:21.458 --> 26:25.083
Before I go and have
a nightcap with Bart Schooner

26:25.083 --> 26:27.791
and get his thoughts on
who should replace him,

26:27.791 --> 26:30.166
let me speak to
what's hanging over the table

26:30.166 --> 26:32.083
and this entire room.

26:32.083 --> 26:35.125
The investigation that
Mr. Dake is conducting.

26:39.333 --> 26:43.333
You all know how to
handle yourselves.

26:43.333 --> 26:46.833
I want you all to cooperate,

26:46.833 --> 26:50.000
to be truthful,
of course.

26:52.750 --> 26:56.083
Because I don't believe
we have anything to worry about.

27:07.500 --> 27:09.166
See what he did?

27:09.166 --> 27:12.791
We handle ourselves and Chuck
gives someone Head of Crim.

27:12.791 --> 27:14.875
Or we cooperate with Dake
and try our luck

27:14.875 --> 27:16.791
starting over with
Chuck's replacement.

27:16.791 --> 27:19.625
Yeah, we saw what he did.

27:25.958 --> 27:27.833
And so
you haven't seen anything

27:27.833 --> 27:29.916
that makes you think
this office is acting

27:29.916 --> 27:32.625
-in an out-of-bounds manner?
-Ambiguous.

27:32.625 --> 27:35.333
Sharpen up the question
so I can give you a good answer.

27:35.333 --> 27:38.166
How would you describe
Mr. Rhoades' tactical approach?

27:38.166 --> 27:39.583
Effective.

27:39.583 --> 27:41.583
And his understanding of
the rules governing behavior?

27:41.583 --> 27:43.500
I can't speak to
his state of mind.

27:43.500 --> 27:47.291
Uh-huh. Let's, uh...

27:47.291 --> 27:50.750
Let's switch gears
for a moment.

27:50.750 --> 27:54.000
Tell me about your meeting
with Axelrod.

27:54.000 --> 27:56.333
The aborted settlement?

27:56.333 --> 27:58.791
No.
Your private meeting.

28:04.041 --> 28:06.375
You tell me how that is

28:06.375 --> 28:08.500
in any way relevant
to your investigation.

28:08.500 --> 28:11.458
I am investigating
all misconduct,

28:11.458 --> 28:13.416
wherever it may be.

28:13.416 --> 28:17.458
And however
an investigation may start,

28:17.458 --> 28:19.333
once I'm in it,

28:19.333 --> 28:22.958
I'm like
a Goddamned octopus --

28:22.958 --> 28:27.750
tentacles out in every
direction, looking, listening,

28:27.750 --> 28:32.625
sucking up every bit of
information that I can find.

28:35.166 --> 28:38.250
Look,
I reported that meeting

28:38.250 --> 28:40.041
the second it was over,

28:40.041 --> 28:42.083
and I have the documentation
to prove it.

28:42.083 --> 28:43.625
Ahhh.

28:43.625 --> 28:46.125
You reported it the next day

28:46.125 --> 28:47.750
in the afternoon.

28:47.750 --> 28:49.000
First chance I got.

28:49.000 --> 28:50.958
Or maybe it took you
that long to decide

28:50.958 --> 28:52.916
what to leave in
and what to leave out.

28:54.375 --> 28:56.208
I left it all in.

28:56.208 --> 28:58.458
Axelrod offered me a job.

28:58.458 --> 29:01.125
This is at the pizzeria
in Yonkers, yes?

29:01.125 --> 29:02.500
That's right.

29:02.500 --> 29:03.750
I turned it down.

29:03.750 --> 29:05.041
Did you?

29:05.041 --> 29:07.000
With no provers in the room,

29:07.000 --> 29:08.250
it's only your word and his.

29:08.250 --> 29:10.833
If I asked Axelrod,
is that how he'd remember it?

29:10.833 --> 29:12.000
Yes.

29:12.000 --> 29:15.000
♪ suspenseful music plays  ♪

29:45.791 --> 29:48.500
Ooh, nice space.

29:48.500 --> 29:49.833
Contained.

29:54.208 --> 29:57.000
I bet your patients
must feel safe here.

30:03.500 --> 30:05.541
You gonna
invite me to sit down?

30:05.541 --> 30:07.500
No.

30:17.708 --> 30:19.708
If you knew enough
to make an appointment

30:19.708 --> 30:21.083
under an assumed name,
you knew

30:21.083 --> 30:23.541
-I didn't want to see you.
-I knew you wouldn't,

30:23.541 --> 30:25.625
but that's not the same
as not wanting to.

30:25.625 --> 30:27.833
Yes, it is.

30:32.375 --> 30:35.750
There's this thing that happens
when we're in a room together.

30:37.208 --> 30:41.125
It always has, Bobby.
It just flows like this.

30:41.125 --> 30:44.166
But I'm shutting it off.

30:44.166 --> 30:46.250
I have shut it off.

30:46.250 --> 30:49.250
Okay.

30:49.250 --> 30:51.625
First, I apologized.

30:51.625 --> 30:54.125
But if it takes me sending you
flowers every day,

30:54.125 --> 30:56.875
Joe DiMaggio style,
to prove it, I will.

30:56.875 --> 30:59.041
He did that
after Marilyn was dead.

30:59.041 --> 31:02.083
Yours would have the same effect
on me that his had on her.

31:02.083 --> 31:04.333
But I need you back
at Axe Capital.

31:04.333 --> 31:06.583
Well,
that's not gonna happen.

31:08.541 --> 31:11.208
Look, there are decisions
I have to make

31:11.208 --> 31:13.458
over actions that I might take,

31:13.458 --> 31:15.625
and I have never had to do it
without you.

31:15.625 --> 31:19.125
The time to recognize that
has long since passed.

31:19.125 --> 31:21.125
We are at
an inflection point.

31:21.125 --> 31:23.000
We have to make big changes
to the company.

31:23.000 --> 31:24.500
We have to make it quickly.

31:24.500 --> 31:29.208
And I am getting conflicting
advice from my people.

31:29.208 --> 31:31.500
The kind of things that

31:31.500 --> 31:34.208
I bounce off you
and it all makes sense.

31:34.208 --> 31:38.250
I know you well enough
to tell you one thing.

31:38.250 --> 31:40.166
You'll figure it out.

31:40.166 --> 31:42.708
You'll connect the dots,
synthesize the information

31:42.708 --> 31:44.541
in a way few others
in this world can.

31:44.541 --> 31:47.041
You always do. It'll be
an amazing thing to see.

31:47.041 --> 31:50.500
But I won't
be there to see it.

31:50.500 --> 31:51.958
What, then?

31:51.958 --> 31:53.250
This?

31:55.708 --> 32:00.583
Just sit here in a nice,
small, well-appointed office,

32:00.583 --> 32:02.791
listen to bullshit
all day long

32:02.791 --> 32:04.750
from people who are
half as smart as us?

32:04.750 --> 32:07.458
I don't know. I was thinking
maybe another hedge fund.

32:07.458 --> 32:08.958
Oh, is that right?

32:08.958 --> 32:10.958
Yeah, I was at another one
the other day.

32:10.958 --> 32:12.708
I won't tell you which,
so don't ask.

32:12.708 --> 32:15.750
And the manager played
some heavy game theory on me,

32:15.750 --> 32:18.375
boxed me into a spot,
essentially put himself

32:18.375 --> 32:20.500
in a position to win
no matter what I said.

32:20.500 --> 32:23.083
I know who it is. I can tell
already by what you said.

32:23.083 --> 32:26.125
Well, I'm tired of being on the
losing side of that paradigm.

32:26.125 --> 32:28.125
-He was looking to hire you?
-Yeah.

32:28.125 --> 32:31.208
That motherfucker is just trying
to poach my most valued --

32:31.208 --> 32:33.666
I'm not your anything.

32:36.375 --> 32:39.041
I'm not gonna kick you out.

32:39.041 --> 32:41.833
But I am asking you
to respect my wishes.

32:41.833 --> 32:43.916
Can you do that?

32:46.375 --> 32:48.250
Okay.

32:53.125 --> 32:55.708
And don't send flowers.

32:55.708 --> 32:57.750
Eva's allergic.

33:02.041 --> 33:03.875
Gene therapy
is finally bearing fruit.

33:03.875 --> 33:05.458
-There's a great company --
-Next.

33:05.458 --> 33:07.791
We buy an algorithm.
I know a guy from Wharton

33:07.791 --> 33:09.041
- with a --

33:09.041 --> 33:11.500
We should go to cash,
take some time off, and --

33:11.500 --> 33:14.208
Okay, fuck this. Do any of you
have juice with Raya?

33:14.208 --> 33:15.458
I could
build a model for it.

33:15.458 --> 33:18.041
I don't want to invest in it.
I want to get on it.

33:18.041 --> 33:19.750
-What is that?
-High-end hookup app.

33:19.750 --> 33:23.083
-Tinder for the rich and famous.
-That's so reductive.

33:23.083 --> 33:25.916
It's exclusive,
and it's about connection.

33:25.916 --> 33:27.500
I was saying
with cash on hand --

33:27.500 --> 33:29.083
Stop talking.

33:29.083 --> 33:31.666
I'm not gonna take any of this
dog shit back to Axe.

33:31.666 --> 33:33.250
It's time for you folks to
sharpen your pencils,

33:33.250 --> 33:36.250
and you better come back
with one Traci Lords of an idea.

33:36.250 --> 33:38.458
And if you need that fucking
defined, here it is.

33:38.458 --> 33:40.250
A barely legal,
market-dominating,

33:40.250 --> 33:44.208
brilliant cocksucker
of an idea.

33:51.291 --> 33:53.458
Thanks for working
through lunch.

33:53.458 --> 33:56.583
I've got to dump five million
shares of Bluudhorn Steel at 40.

33:56.583 --> 33:58.500
Problem is,
the trade's by appointment.

33:58.500 --> 34:00.291
No broker will take
all five million

34:00.291 --> 34:02.166
and guarantee my price,

34:02.166 --> 34:05.041
so I've got five brokers
selling a million each,

34:05.041 --> 34:06.791
and they don't
know about each other.

34:06.791 --> 34:09.083
Are you sure about
the way you're unloading that?

34:09.083 --> 34:11.166
It's kind of shady
and not very efficient.

34:11.166 --> 34:13.000
They'll find out
and ding you later.

34:13.000 --> 34:14.791
I've got to get the price.

34:14.791 --> 34:17.000
You heard what Axe said.
Survive or die.

34:17.000 --> 34:20.208
What if you create
a zero-cost collar?

34:20.208 --> 34:22.416
Right...

34:22.416 --> 34:24.958
Use options
to protect the sale.

34:24.958 --> 34:27.083
Buy $40 puts in Bluudhorn,

34:27.083 --> 34:29.750
then sell $45 calls
to offset the purchase.

34:29.750 --> 34:31.375
You've got free protection
at $40.

34:31.375 --> 34:33.208
The maximum downside
is protected.

34:33.208 --> 34:34.458
But now you can be patient,

34:34.458 --> 34:36.416
and you don't have to
lean on the stock.

34:36.416 --> 34:38.208
You're right.

34:38.208 --> 34:41.000
That'll save us ten million
on this trade.

34:41.000 --> 34:43.666
This is why I need to keep you
when your internship's over.

34:43.666 --> 34:46.250
Yes. I'd believe the same thing
were I you.

34:46.250 --> 34:49.083
Oh.
I ordered you lunch.

