40:53.041 --> 40:55.458
I'd like him to be
good and gone.

40:55.458 --> 40:57.333
Now,
I need to know who sent him

40:57.333 --> 40:59.125
and what they hope
to accomplish.

41:01.125 --> 41:04.833
Are you familiar with the origin
of the word "billet"?

41:04.833 --> 41:06.375
Is this another
"Hamilton" thing?

41:06.375 --> 41:08.458
-No.
-Well, then, yes.

41:08.458 --> 41:10.125
It came from the French

41:10.125 --> 41:12.916
to mean an order to allow
a soldier to live in your home.

41:12.916 --> 41:17.041
But what it's come to mean
is a post or position

41:17.041 --> 41:19.333
and responsibilities
that go along with it.

41:19.333 --> 41:22.541
So my billet
is to be a judge

41:22.541 --> 41:24.208
and adjudicate
on various matters

41:24.208 --> 41:26.458
as put forth
and et cetera.

41:26.458 --> 41:28.083
It is not,
and will never be,

41:28.083 --> 41:30.916
to do your bidding.

41:30.916 --> 41:33.166
I forgot to say please,
didn't I?

41:33.166 --> 41:36.083
I'm working on that.

41:36.083 --> 41:37.500
Please?

41:37.500 --> 41:39.250
Always a lovely word
to hear,

41:39.250 --> 41:41.250
but I'm not
some deputy anymore.

41:41.250 --> 41:42.750
Oh, no.

41:42.750 --> 41:46.083
Uh, I get that
and respect it.

41:46.083 --> 41:49.541
But we both know why
you're not a deputy anymore,

41:49.541 --> 41:52.166
